    "result": {"data":{"challengeNode":{"challenge":{"videoId":null,"videoLocaleIds":null,"bilibiliIds":null,"title":"Task 27","description":"<section id=\"description\">\n<p>The word <code>never</code> is an adverb used to mean <code>not at any time</code> or <code>not ever</code>. It's often used to talk about things that someone doesn't do or hasn't done. For example:</p>\n<p><code>I have never been to Australia.</code> (this means the person has not visited Australia at any time)\n<code>She never eats fast food.</code> (this means she does not eat fast food at any time)</p>\n<p>The word <code>thought</code> is the past tense of <code>think</code>. <code>Thought of that</code> means to have considered or come up with an idea in the past. For example:</p>\n<p><code>I thought of going to the beach, but it was too cold.</code> (this means the person considered going to the beach)</p>\n</section>","challengeType":19,"helpCategory":"English","superBlock":"a2-english-for-developers","block":"learn-how-to-discuss-your-morning-or-evening-routine","fields":{"slug":"/learn/a2-english-for-developers/learn-how-to-discuss-your-morning-or-evening-routine/task-27","blockName":"learn-how-to-discuss-your-morning-or-evening-routine","tests":[]},"question":{"text":"<p>What does James mean when he says, <code>I had never thought of that</code>?</p>","answers":[{"answer":"<p>He had not considered that idea before</p>","feedback":null},{"answer":"<p>He frequently thinks about that</p>","feedback":"<p><code>Never</code> indicates the absence of an action or thought, so it means he had not thought about it, not that he frequently does.</p>"},{"answer":"<p>He always avoids thinking about that</p>","feedback":"<p><code>Never thought of that</code> means he hadn't considered it, not necessarily that he actively avoids it.</p>"},{"answer":"<p>He occasionally thinks about that</p>","feedback":"<p><code>Never</code> suggests it hasn't happened at any time, so it's not about occasional thoughts.</p>"}],"solution":1},"scene":{"setup":{"background":"company2-breakroom.png","characters":[{"character":"James","position":{"x":50,"y":15,"z":1.2},"opacity":0}],"audio":{"filename":"2.2-1.mp3","startTime":1,"startTimestamp":48.56,"finishTimestamp":52.1},"alwaysShowDialogue":null},"commands":[{"background":null,"character":"James","position":null,"opacity":1,"startTime":0,"finishTime":null,"dialogue":null},{"background":null,"character":"James","position":null,"opacity":null,"startTime":1,"finishTime":4.54,"dialogue":{"text":"An early coffee and then breakfast. I had never thought of that.","align":"center"}},{"background":null,"character":"James","position":null,"opacity":0,"startTime":5.04,"finishTime":null,"dialogue":null}]},"translationPending":false,"assignments":[],"audioPath":null}}},"pageContext":{"challengeMeta":{"blockHashSlug":"/learn/a2-english-for-developers/#learn-how-to-discuss-your-morning-or-evening-routine","dashedName":"task-27","certification":"a2-english-for-developers","disableLoopProtectTests":false,"disableLoopProtectPreview":false,"superBlock":"a2-english-for-developers","block":"learn-how-to-discuss-your-morning-or-evening-routine","isFirstStep":false,"template":null,"required":[],"nextBlock":"learn-how-to-discuss-your-morning-or-evening-routine","nextChallengePath":"/learn/a2-english-for-developers/learn-how-to-discuss-your-morning-or-evening-routine/task-28","prevChallengePath":"/learn/a2-english-for-developers/learn-how-to-discuss-your-morning-or-evening-routine/task-26","id":"6557d782bc7613c06aa7dafd"},"projectPreview":{"showProjectPreview":false,"challengeData":{"challengeType":22,"challengeFiles":[]}},"slug":"/learn/a2-english-for-developers/learn-how-to-discuss-your-morning-or-evening-routine/task-27"}},
